.TH "bio_truncate" 9 "bio_truncate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bio_truncate \- truncate the bio to small size of @new_size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bio_truncate
.BI "(struct bio *bio "  ","
.BI "unsigned new_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bio" 12
the bio to be truncated
.IP "new_size" 12
new size for truncating the bio
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Truncate the bio to new size of \fInew_size\fP. If bio_op(bio) is
REQ_OP_READ, zero the truncated part. This function should only
be used for handling corner cases, such as bio eod.
